<p>The abuelo likes to make a small fire outside of his room to keep himself warm.</p>

<h2 id="chickens">Chickens!</h2>

<p>In the midst of the chaos and business of daily life here, we are still looking for ways to grow, and help those around us succeed. We are currently taking the first steps to plan and implement a chicken project! One month, the women who receive groceries will receive a smaller bag, but in addition two chickens. These chickens have been raised in a similar climate and will easily adapt to Santa Maria. Our goal is to have the women raise chickens, but also give them the option of selling us the eggs for use in our feeding program. On average we use fifteen dozen eggs a week here! Many of these women also attend our monthly womenâ€™s group at our community center where they learn valuable life skills to grow as individuals and assist them in providing for their families. We are hoping to put this plan into action this month, and will keep you all updated with the progress.</p>

